  "text": "A total of 59 DINs were included in the analysis. To reduce the dimensionality of the original dataset, we used principal component analysis (PCA). This served two major purposes: first it allowed us to validate our earlier, inspection-based classification scheme [CITATION_1] by a datadriven method; second, it allowed us to explain a substantial part of the variance in the codingspace of the DINs, using a minimal set of orthogonal axes. The number of meaningful axes was determined by use of the Kaiser-Guttman criterion. This criterion includes only principal components (PC), i.e., axes of the coding-space, which explain a larger fraction of the total variance than any of the twelve original variables would (1/12 = 8.3%).",
